claim.claim-text:
1. A retractable cord reel assembly, comprising: 
a) a housing; 
b) a spool rotatably mounted in said housing; 
c) a first cable at least partly carried by said spool; 
d) a second cable at least partly carried by said spool: and 
e) means for releasably coupling said first cable to said second cable when said first and second cables are co-wound together onto said spool.

18. A retractable cord reel assembly comprising: 
a) a housing; 
b) a spool mounted for rotation in said housing; 
c) an electrical component carried by said spool; 
d) a first cable having a first end connected to said electrical component, said first cable being windable onto and off of said spool, said first cable having a longitudinal cavity; and 
e) a second cable having a first end connected to said electrical component, said second cable being windable onto and off of said spool, said second cable being releasably nested in said cavity of said first cable when said cables are co-wound on said spool.

20. A retractable cord reel assembly, comprising: 
a) a spool; 
b) a first cable having a plurality of conductors and at least one longitudinal cavity formed in said cable, said first cable at least partly carried by said spool; 
c) a second cable at least partly carried by said spool; and 
d) a housing, said spool being rotatably mounted in said housing and having at least one guide member mounted on said housing for guiding said second cable to nest into said cavity in said first cable on retraction of said cables onto said spool.

22. A nested pair of cables, comprising a first cable having at least one longitudinal cavity; 
a second cable releasably nested in said cavity; and 
wherein said first and second cables may be nested together or separated in whole or in part.
